text: On 31 January and 1 February 1953, large parts of the Netherlands, Belgium and the United Kingdom were flooded because of a storm. Over 2,500 people were killed. ==References== Category:1953 in Europe Category:1950s in the United Kingdom Category:20th century in Belgium Category:20th century in the Netherlands Category:Disasters in the 1950s Category:Disasters in the United Kingdom Category:Floods in Europe Category:1950s in weather
